  <T n="name">0xFF3714EA<!--String: "Sickness"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP01\UI\Icons\Tutorial\Client\GetToWork\EP01_Sickness_01.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5620a3e4fd79119d</T>
      <T n="text">0xD9E3CAC7<!--String: "From time to time, Sims of any age can come down with some sickness symptoms. This can range from coughs and stuffy noses to polka dot like skin patterns."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP01\UI\Icons\Tutorial\Client\GetToWork\EP01_Sickness_02.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5620a3e4fd79119e</T>
      <T n="text">0x15D4FAE1<!--String: "Sicknesses can be contagious - socializing with a sick Sim is a sure way to contract a bug. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP01\UI\Icons\Tutorial\Client\GetToWork\EP01_Sickness_03.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5620a3e4fd79119f</T>
      <T n="text">0xC3453FC8<!--String: "When a Sim is sick, they can call in to miss work or school from the phone. If you are feeling brave, you can try calling in sick when your Sim is not sick, but that will only work so many times till the boss catches on. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP01\UI\Icons\Tutorial\Client\GetToWork\EP01_Sickness_04.png">2f7d0004:00000000:5620a3e4fd791198</T>
      <T n="text">0x57E7934C<!--String: "To get better, Sims should get plenty of sleep, drink orange juice, or order medicine from the Computer. Your Sim should probably not try drinking medicine if NOT sick."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
